Source:  Forest & Bird
Author:
Vol / Page:  No. 304/17
Edition:
Quote:  [Hdg] Takitimu gecko. In 1966, A Department of Conservation field worker, Tony Jewell, found a very unusual gecko on a scree in the Takitimu Mountains in western Southland... Tony Jewell captured three more Takitimu gecko in 2000, and another in 2001, all from the same scree.
Notes:

Date:  0/6/2007
Source:  Conservation Action
Author:
Vol / Page:  6
Edition:
Quote:  DOC Biodiversity ranger Ros Cole confirmed that this was the first Takitimu gecko to be found in the southern Fiordland area. "The find follows a 2005 discovery, which was the first indication that Takitimu geckos are capable of living in both alpine and forest environments."
